-- European Coal Price Has Biggest Drop in More Than a Week
-- B y   M a r e k   S t r z e l e c k i
-- 2012-12-04T15:35:43Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-04/european-coal-price-has-biggest-drop-in-more-than-a-week.html
European coal for 2013 delivery rose
to its highest level in more than two months.  Thermal coal for delivery next year to Amsterdam, Rotterdam
or Antwerp advanced as much as 0.5 percent to $97.60 a metric
ton, its highest level since Sept. 27, according to broker data
compiled by Bloomberg. The contract traded at $97.20 a metric
ton at 3:25 p.m. in  London .  Bloomberg tracks information from ICAP Plc, GFI Group Inc.,
Marex Spectron Group Ltd., Credit Suisse Group AG, IHS
McCloskey, Tradition Financial Services and Tullett Prebon Plc.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Marek Strzelecki in Warsaw 
